SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1035
By Hensley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the 2026 Mule Day
Court Second Runner-Up, Graciee Katherine
English.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
young citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as
outstanding Tennesseans of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Graciee Katherine English, who was
recently selected as the 2026 Mule Day Court Second Runner-Up; and
WHEREAS, the daughter of Brad and Leslie English of Mt. Pleasant, Ms. English is a
graduate of Freed-Hardeman University, where she played volleyball while earning two
degrees—one in kinesiology with an emphasis in health and human performance and one in
secondary education; and
WHEREAS, Graciee English now serves as a physical education teacher and coach,
and she owns a small business, Stitches by Graciee; and
WHEREAS, Ms. English's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her family, her community, and the citizens of Maury County; and
WHEREAS, the Mule Day Queen and her court play a prominent role in the promotion of
Mule Day, participating in media interviews and serving as hostesses during the festivities; and
WHEREAS, 2026 Mule Day Court Second Runner-Up Graciee English epitomizes the
spirit of distinction and the commitment to greatness that are characteristic of true
Tennesseans; her dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect and admiration of
this body; and
SJR1035
016787
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to pause in their
deliberations to acknowledge and applaud this young woman for her remarkable achievement;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Graciee Katherine
English upon being selected as the 2026 Mule Day Court Second Runner-Up, extending to her
our best wishes for every future success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
